Protests against gender-based violence are continuing in Cape Town on Friday. Courtesy of #DSTV403 CAPE TOWN - Protests against gender-based violence are continuing in Cape Town albeit in smaller numbers on Friday. READ: Five facts: Femicide in South Africa Demonstrators moved to the Cape Town International Convention Centre where the World Economic Forum is underway. Heavy police and private security presence using barbed wire as a barrier to accessing the venue kept protestors at bay.